2016    /**
2017     *  Clones the given element.<br>
2018     *  <br>The clone will be semantically identical to the given element (it
2019     *  looks the same in the final output), but it will not be of the same
2020     *  Java type.
2021     *
2022     *  @param  element The element to clone.
2023     *  @return The clone.
2024     */
2025    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
2026    public static final SVGElement cloneElement( final SVGElement element )
2027    {
2028        final var elementName = requireNonNullArgument( element, "element" ).getElementName();
2029        final var xmlElement = ((XMLElementAdapter) element);
2030        final var flags = xmlElement.getFlags().toArray( Flags[]::new );
2031        final var retValue = new SVGGenericElement( elementName, flags );
2032
2033        retValue.registerValidAttributes( xmlElement.retrieveValidAttributes().toArray( String []::new ) );
2034        retValue.registerValidChildren( xmlElement.retrieveValidChildren().toArray( String []::new ) );
2035
2036        element.getAttributes().forEach( retValue::setAttribute );
2037        element.getChildren().forEach( c -> retValue.addChild( cloneElement( (SVGElement) c ) ) );
2038        element.getNamespaces().forEach( retValue::setNamespace );
2039
2040        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
2041        return retValue;
2042    }   //  cloneElement()

2513    /**
2514     *  Creates an SVG {@code <svg>} element instance.
2515     *
2516     *  @param  usage  How the new {@code <svg>} element should be used.
2517     *  @return The new {@code <svg>} element.
2518     */
2519    @API( status = STABLE, since = "0.0.5" )
2520    public static final SVG createSVG( final Usage usage )
2521    {
2522        final var retValue = new SVGImpl();
2523
2524        switch( requireNonNullArgument( usage, "usage" ) )
2525        {
2526            case EMBED_HTML ->
2527            {
2528                retValue.setNamespace( createSVGNamespace( SVG_PREFIX ) );
2529                retValue.setNamespace( createXLINKNamespace() );
2530                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_BaseProfile, "full" );
2531                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_Version, "1.1" );
2532            }
2533
2534            case EMBED_HTML5 ->
2535            {
2536                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_BaseProfile, "full" );
2537                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_Version, "1.1" );
2538            }
2539
2540            case EMBED_SVG -> { /* Does nothing */ }
2541
2542            case STANDALONE_DOCUMENT ->
2543            {
2544                /*
2545                 * This configuration was taken more or less (more <i>less</i>)
2546                 * from an SVG document created with Inkscape.
2547                 */
2548                retValue.setNamespace( createSVGNamespace( SVG_PREFIX ) );
2549                retValue.setNamespace( createSVGNamespace( EMPTY_STRING ) );
2550                retValue.setNamespace( createXLINKNamespace() );
2551                retValue.setNamespace( createCCNamespace() );
2552                retValue.setNamespace( createRDFNamespace() );
2553                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_BaseProfile, "full" );
2554                retValue.setAttribute( SVGATTRIBUTE_Version, "1.1" );
2555            }
2556
2557            default -> throw new UnsupportedEnumError( usage );
2558        }
2559
2560        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
2561        return retValue;
2562    }   //  createSVG()
